{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_016miCyqrUcpTYW7KF5Tb6C9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. `ObjectMetadataModified` only checks top-level labels, not annotations or pod template annotations. So the `deploymentSpecModified` function in istiocsr also doesn't compare pod template annotations. I need to add that comparison so the idempotency guard works properly — when the hash annotation changes, the deployment will be detected as modified and updated.\n\nNow I have the full picture. Here's my complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Complete Implementation\n\nThe implementation mirrors the trust-manager pattern: read the CNO-injected CA ConfigMap, compute a SHA-256 hash of the PEM data, stamp it as a pod template annotation on the IstioCSR Deployment, and skip the update when the hash hasn't changed.\n\n### Files to modify\n\n---\n\n### 1. `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go` — Add the hash annotation constant\n\nAdd after the `IstiocsrCAKeyName` constant (line 89):\n\n```go\n// caBundleHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the CA bundle hash.\n// When the hash changes, the annotation update triggers a rolling restart of the IstioCSR pods.\ncaBundleHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-bundle-hash\"\n```\n\nThe full constants block (lines 82–90) becomes:\n\n```go\n\t// IstiocsrCAConfigMapName is the name of the configmap which is mounted in istiocsr container, containing the\n\t// CA certificate configured in the secret referenced in the issuer.\n\tIstiocsrCAConfigMapName = istiocsrCommonName + \"-issuer-ca-copy\"\n\n\t// IstiocsrCAKeyName is the key name holding the CA certificate in the issuer secret or the controller\n\t// CA configmap.\n\tIstiocsrCAKeyName = \"ca.crt\"\n\n\t// caBundleHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the CA bundle hash.\n\tcaBundleHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-bundle-hash\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go` — New file with `readCABundleHash` and `computeCABundleHash`\n\nCreate this new file:\n\n**File: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go`**\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/sha256\"\n\t\"encoding/hex\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common\"\n)\n\n// readCABundleHash reads the CNO-injected CA bundle ConfigMap from the operator\n// namespace and returns the SHA-256 hash of its PEM content.\n// Returns (\"\", nil) when the ConfigMap or key is not found, allowing the\n// controller to proceed without a hash when the CA bundle is not yet injected.\nfunc (r *Reconciler) readCABundleHash() (string, error) {\n\tcm := &corev1.ConfigMap{}\n\tkey := client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tNamespace: common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\tName:      common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName,\n\t}\n\tif err := r.Get(r.ctx, key, cm); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(\n\t\t\terr,\n\t\t\t\"failed to read CA bundle ConfigMap %q in namespace %q\",\n\t\t\tcommon.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName, common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\t)\n\t}\n\n\tcaBundle, ok := cm.Data[common.TrustedCABundleKey]\n\tif !ok || caBundle == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\n\t\t\t\"CA bundle ConfigMap %q does not contain key %q\",\n\t\t\tcommon.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName, common.TrustedCABundleKey,\n\t\t)\n\t}\n\n\treturn computeCABundleHash(caBundle), nil\n}\n\n// computeCABundleHash returns the SHA-256 hex digest of the CA bundle PEM content.\nfunc computeCABundleHash(caBundle string) string {\n\thash := sha256.Sum256([]byte(caBundle))\n\treturn hex.EncodeToString(hash[:])\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go` — Stamp the hash annotation and add idempotency guard\n\n**Change 1:** Modify `createOrApplyDeployments` signature to accept `caBundleHash string`:\n\nReplace line 31:\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) createOr